flowchart TD
  A[Trigger: Start of BIW assembly process for a new production batch.]
  A --> N1[Stream: DDM/Crawlers - Retrieve build specifications and inventory levels from SAP S/4HANA.]
  N1 --> N2[Cortex: AutoML - Analyze historical assembly data to identify optimal sequences and parameters.]
  N2 --> N3[Cortex: Data Quality & Validation - Validate optimized sequences against current inventory and build specifications.]
  N3 --> N4[PB: Remote Functions - Adjust assembly sequences and parameters in SAP S/4HANA.]
  N4 --> N5[PB: Remote Functions - Schedule quality gate inspections based on optimized sequences.]
  N5 --> N6{Decision: Optimize BIW assembly/welding sequence, parameters, and quality-release criteria to minimize COGS while meeting build specifications and quality targets.}
  N5 --> Z1[Outcome: Reduced COGS, minimized changeovers, fewer scrapped/reworked BIW panels, and on-time delivery of BIW assemblies.]
  N6 -->|Insufficient inventory for optimal se...| B1[Adjust sequence to available inventory and notify stakeholders.]
  B1 --> O1[Outcome: Suboptimal but feasible assembly plan.]
  O1 --> End[End]
  N6 -->|Quality gate inspection fails| B2[Initiate rework process and update assembly schedule.]
  B2 --> O2[Outcome: Corrective actions taken to meet quality standards.]
  O2 --> End[End]
  N6 -->|Unexpected equipment downtime| B3[Re-optimize assembly sequences to account for downtime.]
  B3 --> O3[Outcome: Adjusted assembly plan to maintain on-time delivery.]
  O3 --> End[End]
  Z1 --> End[End]